main event: An unidentified aerial object was observed in the Green River Lakes area of Wyoming on October 5, 1953.
interesting points: The object displayed a bright bluish-green color and had erratic motion with varying degrees of brightness,Its course was described as stationary with periods of bright intensity,Observers noted that the star Vomahaut was low on the horizon during the sighting, which could account for the object's refractibility,Observations lasted approximately 15 to 17 minutes.
witness description: a surgeon who reported the sighting
